@startuml
title Booking creation and cancellation sequence

actor User
participant Frontend
participant API
database Database
participant "Payment Service" as Payment
participant "Email Service" as Email

User -> Frontend: Select room and dates
Frontend -> API: Check availability
API -> Database: Check room availability

alt Room is available
    Database --> API: Room is available
    API --> Frontend: Room is available

    User -> Frontend: Confirm booking
    Frontend -> API: POST /booking
    API -> Payment: Process payment

    alt Payment successful
        Payment --> API: Payment successful
        API -> Database: Create booking
        Database --> API: Booking created
        API -> Email: Send booking confirmation
        Email --> API: Confirmation sent
        API --> Frontend: 201 Created
        Frontend --> User: Show booking confirmation

        User -> Frontend: Cancel booking
        Frontend -> API: DELETE /booking/{id}
        API -> Database: Cancel booking
        Database --> API: Booking cancelled
        API -> Email: Send cancellation email
        Email --> API: Cancellation email sent
        API --> Frontend: 200 OK
        Frontend --> User: Show cancellation confirmation

    else Payment failed
        Payment --> API: Payment failed
        API --> Frontend: 402 Payment Required
        Frontend --> User: Show payment failed message
    end

else Room is not available
    Database --> API: Room is not available
    API --> Frontend: 409 Conflict
    Frontend --> User: Show room unavailable message
end

@enduml